iblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">770</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ξύμπας Ἀχαιῶν λαός</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg006.perseus-grc1:1243\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ph.\">Ph.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1243</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg004.perseus-grc1:144\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ OT\">OT</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">144</biblScope></bibl>, etc.; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἱππόται λαοί</foreign>, i.e. the Thessalians, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg002.perseus-grc1:4:153\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ P.\">P.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.153</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg002.perseus-grc1:9:54\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.54</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg003.perseus-grc1:1:17\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">N.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.17</biblScope></bibl>. (The resemblance between <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λαός</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">people</tr_> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λᾶος</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">stone</tr_> (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λᾶας</foreign>) is implied in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:24:611\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">24.611</biblScope> </bibl> <forei